    <h2 class="review_top-title review_margin-top">Account Types</h2>
    <p class="review_top-text review_margin-top">In order to serve a variety of needs of different traders, Pepperstone has acquired a rather unusual approach toward account type. It offers four different account types including:</p>
    <p class="review_top-text review_margin-top"><b>Edge Standard Account </b>- This account features zero commission, STP processing, Automated Risk Management System, liquidity from 22 banks and ECNs, interbank spreads and negative balance protection.</p>
    <p class="review_top-text review_margin-top"><b>Edge Razor Account </b> - For this account, traders need to deposit a minimum of $200 AUD. This account allows traders to trade in a wide range of currencies including HKD, SGD, NZD, CHF, CAD, EUR, GBP, JPY, USD and AUD. The account allows EAs, scalping and hedging and features ECN commission, leverage of 500:1, Raw Interbank Direct Pricing and trade size range of 0.01 lots to 100 lots.</p>
    <p class="review_top-text review_margin-top"><b>Edge Swap Free Account  </b>- For this account, traders need to deposit a minimum of $200 AUD. It works with USD, AUD, SGD and EUR. The account allows EAs, scalping and hedging and features zero commission, Sharia compliance, and straight through processing and trade size range of 0.01 lots to 100 lots.</p>
    <p class="review_top-text review_margin-top"><b>Edge Active Traders Account  </b>- The account is made for investors who trade in high volume or are institutional investors. It provides advanced level reporting plus custom solutions such as FX GUI and API along with other third party platforms. You also get your own relationship manager and a separate account with VPS hosting.</p>
